{"TopicId":178937,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Chandra X-ray Observatory shut down...","CreatedByName":"Cassel","CreatedById":181728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T19:28:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cassel","CreatedById":181728,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T19:28:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is very strange that first New Mexico observatory was closed, then Hubble went into safe-mode and now this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://phys.org/news/2018-10-nasa-space-telescope-orbit.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://phys.org/news/2018-10-nasa-space-telescope-orbit.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T19:44:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s clear that aliens are shutting down our capabilities as a start for an invasion.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAfter all, isn\u0027t the next end of the world about to happen? There are so many of them I keep losing track.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlternatively, IIRC Hubble is about 30, and Chandra almost 20 years old. Hardware breaks down. With so many observatories and space related hardware around, I\u0027d be surprised if no coincidental timing was ever recorded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T19:49:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKepler, Hubble, and now Chandra... and at the rate JWST is being delayed and all of the problems it\u0027s facing...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve got TESS but that\u0027s a different kind of telescope entirely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scotius","CreatedById":57622,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-13T22:29:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinal months of 2018 are shaping up to be bad for space exploration. Accidents, malfunctions, delays abound. Here\u0027s hoping 2019 will be much kinder to us \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XB-70A","CreatedById":144985,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-14T01:54:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539460167\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe\u0027ve got TESS but that\u0027s a different kind of telescope entirely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust for the NASA, and in the department of \u003Cem\u003EChandra\u003C/em\u003E, HETE-2 and NuSTAR could potentially help to keep a good rate of data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, could it be the\u00A0occasion for \u003Cem\u003ENewton\u003C/em\u003E to get back the enthusiasts interest? If I remember correctly, it is as old\u00A0as\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EChandra\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-14T02:17:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467332\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539482098\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144985\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XB-70A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, XB-70A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust for the NASA, and in the department of \u003Cem\u003EChandra\u003C/em\u003E, HETE-2 and NuSTAR could potentially help to keep a good rate of data.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E Also, could it be the\u00A0occasion for \u003Cem\u003ENewton\u003C/em\u003E to get back the enthusiasts interest? If I remember correctly, it is as old\u00A0as\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EChandra\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow... I looked up Newton because I had no idea what it was and went down a giant Wikipedia rabbit hole... I had no idea that the ESA had so many active and planned science missions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-14T03:18:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467345\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539483425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161505\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ultimate Steve\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Ultimate Steve said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Ehad no idea\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E that the ESA had so many active and planned science missions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nESA focuses most of its budget into scientific probes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223467332\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022178937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221539482098\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144985\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XB-70A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, XB-70A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E it be the\u00A0occasion for \u003Cem\u003ENewton\u003C/em\u003E to get back the enthusiasts \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Einterest\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nXMM-Newton is still active right ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-14T03:19:03Z\u0022 title=\u002210/14/2018 03:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 14, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}